suggestions.title: Focus on 'Chill' and 'Fun' Themes
suggestions.description: The data shows a clear preference for 'Chill' and 'Fun' themed events. Future events should prioritize these themes, exploring variations within them (e.g., 'Chill Beach Day,' 'Fun Game Night').  Solicit feedback through pre-event surveys to pinpoint specific interests within these broader themes.

suggestions.title: Optimize Event Costs and Explore Free/Low-Cost Activities
suggestions.description: The average cost of 750,000 VND per event can be optimized.  The June 2025 event demonstrated a successful, high-rated event at a significantly lower cost (450,000 VND). Analyze the cost breakdown of past events to identify areas for savings.  Consider incorporating free or low-cost activities like potlucks, outdoor games, or volunteer work to reduce expenses without sacrificing engagement.

suggestions.title: Increase Activity Variety and Pre-Event Engagement
suggestions.description: While 'Chill' and 'Fun' are preferred themes, the activities within them have lacked variety. Offer a broader range of activities catering to different interests within each theme. For example, a 'Fun' theme could include a cooking class, escape room, or themed party. Implement pre-event surveys or polls to gauge interest and tailor activities accordingly, increasing participation and satisfaction.

suggestions.title: Improve Event Timing and Scheduling
suggestions.description: The data lacks specific timing information (day of the week, time of day). Gather data on participant availability and preferences for event timing. Experiment with different days and times to maximize attendance and engagement. For example, Friday evenings or weekend brunches might be more convenient for some teams.

suggestions.title: Diversify Event Locations
suggestions.description: The data doesn't specify event locations. Explore different venues and settings that align with the chosen theme and activities. Consider outdoor spaces, unique restaurants, or activity-specific venues (e.g., bowling alleys, art studios). Varying locations can add novelty and excitement to future events.
